HEADWORD: Federalist
<hw>Fed"er*al*ist</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>f⟦eacute⟧d⟦eacute⟧raliste</ets>.]</ety> <def>An advocate of
confederation; specifically <fld>(Amer. Hist.)</fld>, a friend of the
Constitution of the United States at its formation and adoption; a
member of the political party which favored the administration of
president Washington.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

